               <msContents class="#MTM">
                  <summary> "Cāstiram - 12" ("12 Treatises") is a multi-text  (possibly composite?) manuscript containing  fragments of 12 works of various authors, which in significant part provide recipes for diverse medical preparations aimed at rejuvenation (called "kaṟpam").
The manuscript contains following texts:
1.  "Ticaimukakkuru", which  seems to be a fragment (i.e. 22 verses, no. 461-482) of a medical text.
2.  "Kariyuppiṉ vaḷamai" which seems to be text on a medical preparation.
3.  "Veṅkāra kaṭṭu centūram", which seems to be a text on a medical preparation.
4.  "Pañcapūtak kaṭṭuk kucittu [kuccattu] mūlikkai kaṟpam", which   seems to be a text on a medical preparation.
5.  "Viṟumaviruṣattayla kaṟppam", which seems to be a text on a medical preparation.
6.  "Kōṅkam pūkaṟppam", which  seems to be a text on a medical preparation.
7.  "Tirumūlaṉāyaṉār aṉṉūtti [ainnuṟṟi] tiraṭṭukuṟippu", which   seems to be a text in 112 verses.
8.  "Pañcapūtam aṟiya", which seems to be a text on a medical preparation. 
9.   "Ñāṉam", which seems to be a fragment (verses no. 9-10) of a text on yogic practices.
10.  "Pañcāṣṣaramāṟal ", which seems to be a fragment (verses no. 55-58) of a text on yogic practices. 
11.  "Vātam nīti", which  seems to be a text on alchemy in 7 verses. 
12.  "Vayittiyam ", which  seems to be a text on medicine in 9 verses.</summary>
                  
